In addition to the report required in KRS 260.853, the commission shall report to the Governor and to the Legislative Research Commission with respect to industrial hemp policies and practices that will result in the proper legal growing, management, use, and marketing of the state's potential industrial hemp industry. These policies and practices shall, at a minimum, address the following:
Federal laws and regulatory constraints;
The economic and financial feasibility of an industrial hemp market in Kentucky;
Kentucky businesses that utilize industrial hemp;
Examination of research on industrial hemp production and utilization;
The potential for globally marketing Kentucky industrial hemp;
Feasibility study of private funding for the Kentucky industrial hemp research program;
Law enforcement concerns;
Statutory and regulatory schemes for growing of industrial hemp by private producers; and
Technical support and education about industrial hemp.
